# Changelog

All notable changes to the Python CLI boilerplate template will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Added

- **Comprehensive Test Coverage**: Complete test suite covering all 35 CLI standards
  - Tests for help output at root and all subcommands
  - Tests for globbing patterns including recursive `**/*`
  - Tests for stdin processing with `-` flag
  - Tests for JSON vs human output modes
  - Tests for full config precedence chain (CLI > env > local > user > defaults)
  - Tests for exit-code behavior for all error types
  - Tests for all CLI flags and options
  - Tests for daemon mode, TUI mode, health checks, privacy mode, audit logging
  - Tests for structured logging, config reload, deprecation policy

- **Backward Compatibility and Documentation**: Migration guide and comprehensive documentation
  - Migration guide for updating existing generated CLIs
  - Comprehensive README with all features documented
  - Complete CLI flags and options reference
  - Environment variables documentation
  - Exit codes documentation
  - Troubleshooting section
  - Usage examples for all features

### Changed

- **Documentation**: Enhanced README with:
  - Installation instructions
  - Shell completion setup
  - Quick start guide
  - Feature documentation (standard, advanced, conditional)
  - Configuration file format and precedence
  - CLI flags and options tables
  - Environment variables reference
  - Exit codes reference
  - Troubleshooting guide
  - Project structure documentation

### Security

- No security vulnerabilities in this release

### Migration Notes

- No breaking changes - all new features are opt-in via template options
- Existing generated CLIs remain compatible with default template options
- Feature flags via conditional includes ensure backward compatibility
- See [MIGRATION.md](MIGRATION.md) for detailed migration instructions

## [1.0.0] - Initial Release

### Added

- Basic CLI framework with Typer
- File processing with globbing support
- Stdin processing
- JSON output mode
- Color control (auto/always/never)
- Quiet/verbose/debug logging modes
- Shell completion (bash, zsh, fish)
- Error formatting with file references
- Daemon process support (conditional)
- TUI mode support (conditional)
- Progress indicators
- Pager integration
- Terminal awareness
- Security and resource management
- Health check mechanism (conditional)
- Privacy mode (conditional)
- Audit logging (conditional)
- Signal handling (SIGINT, SIGHUP)
- Dry-run mode
- Confirmation prompts with --force flag
- Man page generation
- NO_COLOR environment variable support
- Structured logging with format auto-detection
- Config reload via SIGHUP
- Manual config reload command
- Legacy deprecation policy
- Advanced configuration with validation and migration (conditional)
